SIMPLE: centennial
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Centennial
<hw>Cen*ten"ni*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>centum</ets> a hundred + <ets>annus</ets> year.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Relating to, or associated with, the commemoration of an event that
happened a hundred years before; <as>as, a <ex>centennial</ex>
ode</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Happening once in a hundred years; <as>as,
<ex>centennial</ex> jubilee; a <ex>centennial</ex>
celebration</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Lasting or aged a hundred years.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That opened through long lines⟦br⟧
Of sacred ilex and <qex>centennial</qex> pines.</q>
<rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Centennial</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Centennial
<hw>Cen*ten"ni*al</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The celebration of the
hundredth anniversary of any event; a centenary.</def> <mark>[U.
S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Centennially</ent>⟦br⟧
